than three years in the French capital, he regularly recorded in a journal revealing impressions of Parisian life and also managed to establish various meaningful social contacts, with the intriguing Sophie Ravoux for one. By focusing on this episode, the most important of Jünger’s adult life, the author brings to bear a wide reading of journals and correspondence to reveal Jünger’s professional and personal experience in wartime and thereafter. This new perspective on the war years adds significantly to our understanding of France's darkest hour.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aAuthors, Germany20th centuryvBiography 0aAuthors, Germany20th centuryvBiography. 0aSoldierszGermanyvBiography. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  a20th century.  abiographical.  abiography.  acombat.  acontroversial writers.  aengaging.  aernst junger.  afighting.  afrench history.  afrench intellectuals.  agerman author.  agerman celebrities.  agerman history.  agerman occupation.  agerman officers.  agood vs evil.  aground force invasions.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  ajean cocteau.  ajournaling.  ajournals.  amartin heidegger.  amilitary history.  anazi germany.  anazi paris.  aoccupation of paris.  aparisian life.  apersonal experience.  aprimary historical sources.  arealistic.  asophie ravoux.  awartime.  aworld war ii.  aww ii.1 aBerghahn, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745115640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857451156423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857451156/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-20